div1.p: IN THE UNITED STATE SISTRICT, WESERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON, NORTHERN DIVISION.
IN THE MATTER OF THE APPLICATION OF MRS. GLADYS FREDRIKA FUSON, FOR WRIT OF HABEAS CORPUS.} NO.3451 MOTION TO QUASH

Comes now King Dykeman, respondent named in the writ of habeas corpus issued in the above entitled action, and moves the court for an order quashing the writ of habeas corpus issued herein, dismissing the above entitled motion and remanding the petitioner above named to the custody of the Juvenile Detention Home in King County, Washington, on the ground and for the reason that the petition in this action fails to state facts suffcuent to entitile petitioner to any relief
Alfred H Laudin Frank P. Helsell Attorneys for Respondent.
IN THE DISTRICT COURT WESTER DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON, NORTHERN DIVISION.
IN THE MATTER IF THE APPLICATION OF GLADYS FREDRIKA FUSON FOR A WRIT OF HEBEAS CORPUS
FILED INTHE U.S. District Court Wastern District of washington Oct 27 1916 FRANK L CROSBY Clerk by Edy Laxie Deputy
ALFRED H. LUNDIN FRENK P. HELSELL 432 Court Hourse, Seattle, Wash. Attorneys for Respondednt.
